      "attributes": {
        "title": "S03E09: ILM and data management",
        "slug": "s03e09-ilm-and-data-management",
        "blurb": {
          "html": "<p>For three weeks we will dive into a different topic of Observability using Elastic Stack every day before lunch in the CEST/EST timezone!\nAll you need to do is to be ready at 11:45 CEST/EST.</p>\n"
        },
        "slidedeck": {
          "data": [
            {
              "id": "sd_7425",
              "type": "images",
              "slides": [
                {
                  "id": "sl_scE05x",
                  "type": "image",
                  "title": null,
                  "desc": {
                    "html": "<p>Daily Elastic Observability B(y|i)te\nIndex Lifecycle Management &amp; data streams David Pilato (@dadoonet)</p>\n"
                  },
                  "image": "https://on.notist.cloud/slides/deck7425/large-0.jpg",
                  "html": null
                },
                {
                  "id": "sl_UvwnyM",
                  "type": "image",
                  "title": null,
                  "desc": {
                    "html": "<p>Before data streams •\nOne single index for a use case (for example logs) ‒\nmixing nginx logs with smtp logs (different fields)\n‒\nwith thousand of fields (10k limit)\n‒\nmost fields are empty (bad compression because of sparsity)\n‒\nvery big index mapping</p>\n"
                  },
                  "image": "https://on.notist.cloud/slides/deck7425/large-1.png",
                  "html": null
                },
                {
                  "id": "sl_7Ffbql",
                  "type": "image",
                  "title": null,
                  "desc": {
                    "html": "<p>Data streams •\nOne datastream per dataset\n•\nNaming convention &lt;type&gt;-&lt;dataset&gt;-&lt;namespace&gt; ‒\nlogs-nginx-default, logs-smtp-default\n‒\nmetrics-linux.iostat-default, metrics-system.diskio-default\n•\nData streams must have a matching index template\n•\nDocuments must contain the @timestamp field (configurable)\n•\nfor append-only time series data</p>\n"
                  },
                  "image": "https://on.notist.cloud/slides/deck7425/large-2.png",
                  "html": null
                },
                {
                  "id": "sl_jZOPjA",
                  "type": "image",
                  "title": null,
                  "desc": {
                    "html": "<p>Data streams •\nbacking index .ds-&lt;data-stream&gt;-&lt;yyyy.MM.dd&gt;-&lt;generation&gt;\n•\nrollover and alias ‒\nmany search indices\n‒\none single write index</p>\n"
                  },
                  "image": "https://on.notist.cloud/slides/deck7425/large-3.jpg",
                  "html": null
                },
                {
                  "id": "sl_Lt7DbZ",
                  "type": "image",
                  "title": null,
                  "desc": {
                    "html": "<p>Before ILM •\nTime based indices like filebeat-2021.10.28 ‒\nsome are very small\n‒\nwhat happens for big events (like christmas)?\n‒\nwhat happens when you have unpredictable traﬃc?</p>\n"
                  },
                  "image": "https://on.notist.cloud/slides/deck7425/large-4.png",
                  "html": null
                },
                {
                  "id": "sl_yCq1Ty",
                  "type": "image",
                  "title": null,
                  "desc": {
                    "html": "<p>ILM •\n•\nan ILM policy: ‒\nMight use rollover\n‒\nMight be moved to warm, cold, frozen phases\n‒\nMight be removed\nILM can be applied to data streams</p>\n"
                  },
                  "image": "https://on.notist.cloud/slides/deck7425/large-5.png",
                  "html": null
                },
